<refsection condition="ref.description">
<title>Description</title>

<para>This <tag>table</tag> element identifies a formal
table (one without a <tag>title</tag>). DocBook allows either
<acronym>CALS</acronym> or <acronym>HTML</acronym> tables, both of
which describe tables geometrically using rows, columns, and cells.
</para>

<para>Tables may include column headers and footers with
<tag>thead</tag> and <tag>tfoot</tag>, respectively. Use the <tag class="attribute">rowheader</tag> attribute to identify row headers.
</para>

